{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Chocolate Cake","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line a square baking tin (20 cm) with baking paper.","Place flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda and salt in mixing bowl then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add milk, water and oil then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Finish mixing by hand with spatula then transfer to prepared baking tin.","Bake for 10 minutes (180°C). Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl. Remove cake from tin and allow to cool on a wire rack. Meanwhile, prepare icing."]},{"title":"Icing, Assembly and Decoration","content":["Place white chocolate in mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Add butter and melt <b>2 min\/50°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add cream cheese, icing sugar and vanilla extract then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer icing to a piping bag and set aside.","Use a pastry cutter to cut 24 discs (Ø 4 cm) out of the chocolate cake. Place a disc of sponge cake in the bottom of 8 jars (each jar Ø 5 cm, approx. 80 ml capacity) add 1 tsp Baileys or cream liqueur and top with icing. Repeat process twice more, finishing with a layer of icing. Decorate each jar with 2 raspberries, then close jar lid.","Store in fridge until ready to pack for your picnic."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Chocolate Cake","content":["90 g plain flour","60 g soft brown sugar","15 g cocoa powder","1 tsp baking powder","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","1 pinch fine sea salt","50 g milk","50 g water","40 g sunflower oil, plus extra for greasing"]},{"title":"Icing, Assembly and Decoration","content":["25 g white chocolate, small pieces or callets","15 g butter","100 g cream cheese","15 g icing sugar","½ tsp vanilla extract","24 tsp Baileys, or other cream liqueur (approx. 80 g)","16 fresh raspberries"]}],"id":"r115719","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-E81mYVI1k9Q\/XZWqmUuQNeI\/AAAAAAAAfaY\/Yd6SiFAjmgc23pQeL_lpLe3UcyLEG-dEwCL